body:
Creates a JSON metadata file with information about each module in the design.

Example (from a PyCDE test)
```json
{
    "modules": [
        {
            "module_name": "PolynomialSystem",
            "ports": [
                {
                    "name": "y",
                    "direction": "output",
                    "bits": 32
                }
            ],
            "input_bits": 0,
            "output_bits": 32,
            "inout_bits": 0
        },
        {
            "module_name": "PolyComputeForCoeff_62_42_6",
            "ports": [
                {
                    "name": "x",
                    "direction": "input",
                    "bits": 32
                },
                {
                    "name": "y",
                    "direction": "output",
                    "bits": 32
                }
            ],
            "input_bits": 32,
            "output_bits": 32,
            "inout_bits": 0
        },
        {
            "module_name": "PolyComputeForCoeff_1_2_3_4_5",
            "ports": [
                {
                    "name": "example.y",
                    "direction": "input",
                    "bits": 32
                }
            ],
            "input_bits": 32,
            "output_bits": 0,
            "inout_bits": 0
        }
    ]
}
```
